Several roads in Pietermaritzburg and its surroundings were
closed on Tuesday morning due to flooding caused by the heavy rains that caused
havoc in different parts of the province. Main four low-level bridges in Msunduzi Area - 1. Grimpthorpe Road Low - underwater. 2. Woodhouse Road by the Sobantu Village – underwater. 3. Mason's Mill by Hulamin/Makro area - underwater. 4. Willowfontein by former National Minister of Health Dr. Zweli
Mkhize - underwater. Waterlogged roads 1. Selby Msimang Road by Nyonithwele High School - Edendale
area - road underwater. 2. Selby Msimang Road by DUT Indumiso Campus - road underwater. 3. Washington Road/Jesmond Road next to Msunduzi Traffic and
Security Heads Quarters - the whole road underwater. 4. Moses Mabhida Road/ Devonshire by the Old Prison - incoming
bound was underwater this morning. 5. Willowton Rd just before Ohrtmann Road by The Witness
News Papers – the road was underwater. 6. Ohrtmann Road/Royston Road by Albany Bakeries - Road was underwater
this morning. 7. Sobantu Village at Maflethin Dark City area - right down
at the traffic circle – road was underwater.